docs {
  # Get Saved View by ID

  Returns a single saved view configuration.

  ## Path Parameters

  | Param | Description |
  |-------|-------------|
  | id | Saved view identifier (e.g., `view-001`, `view-002`) |

  ## Response Shape

  ```json
  {
    "id": "view-001",
    "userId": "user-001",
    "name": "System 1 vs System 2 Comparison",
    "chartConfigurationId": "chart-interactivity",
    "selectedSystems": ["system1", "system2"],
    "filters": {
      "modelId": "deepseek-r1",
      "division": "closed"
    },
    "normalization": {
      "enabled": false,
      "overrides": {}
    },
    "layers": [],
    "createdAt": "2026-01-20T14:30:00Z",
    "updatedAt": "2026-01-20T14:30:00Z"
  }
  ```

  ## Use Case

  Saved views allow users to bookmark specific chart configurations for quick access, including:
  - Which systems to compare
  - Active filters (model, division)
  - Normalization settings
  - Additional visualization layers
}
